title_full:
Zebra Katz

              —
              Less Is Moor
            
              (The Vinyl Factory)
label: The Vinyl Factory
description:
Omnivorous producer/rapper/performer Zebra Katz makes a dead strong impression with his rude debut album of industrial-strength hip hop, ragga jungle prang outs, and sleazy darkroom night slugs.

Fuelled by a fiercely indomitable attitude, ‘Less Is Moor’ follows a steady course of collabs with wayward dance music producers (Hervé, French Fries), rap artists... more

label: Warp Records
description:
Few surprises here from superproducer Hudson Mohawke who remains possibly one of the most influential artists of the last decade - for better or for worse.

The overdriven trap that made those TNGHT rekkids so special and gave "Yeezus" teeth might not sound as minty fresh as it did in 2012 but there's still plenty to enjoy here. Everything's produced in... more

label: Hyperdub
description:
One of the strongest debut albums we've heard in years, Nazar’s ‘Guerrilla’ is a record about the Angolan civil war that we reckon will come to be one of the defining albums of 2020

label: Bedroom Community
